The article announces several appointments and reappointments to various positions within the US government. Summer K. Mersinger from South Dakota has been appointed as a Commissioner of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission. Marjorie A. Rollinson from Virginia has been appointed as Chief Counsel for the Internal Revenue Service and an Assistant General Counsel in the Department of the Treasury. Suzanne Elizabeth Summerlin from Florida has been appointed as General Counsel of the Federal Labor Relations Authority. Mark Toshiro Uyeda from California has been reappointed as a Member of the Securities and Exchange Commission. David E. White Jr. from New York has been appointed as Deputy Director of the Peace Corps. Gwynne A. Wilcox from New York has been reappointed as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board.